What is more interesting is the broader landscape. Benedict Evans wrote in =
the Financial Times ( https://www.ft.com/content/a2c29506-4a38-47a3-8775-be=
b5e488c169 ) :

Part of the problem and conflict when it comes to discussing AGI is that it=
=E2=80=99s an abstract concept =E2=80=94 a thought experiment =E2=80=94 wit=
hout any clear or well-understood theoretical model. The engineers on the A=
pollo Program knew how far away the moon was and how much thrust the rocket=
 had but we don=E2=80=99t know how far away AGI is, nor how close OpenAI=E2=
=80=99s large language models are, nor whether they can get there=E2=80=A6

Unfortunately for the =E2=80=9Cdoomers=E2=80=9D, the events of the last wee=
k have sped everything up. One of the now resigned board members was quoted=
